# How to use XMonad

## Mod key
Default is the 'alt' key. Can easily be changed to any other key. Currently it is the Windows key!

## Open and Close windows
* Open a Terminal: Mod-Shift-Return
* How to close a Window: Mod-Shift-c
* Start an application: Mod-p to start dmenu application launcher
 
## Managing Panes
* Switch focus forward: Mod-j
* Switch focus backwards: Mod-k
* Move focused pane forwards: Mod Shift-j 
* Move focused pane backward: Mod Shift-k
* Rearrange panes: Mod-Space
* Make current pane Full Screen: Mod-Space Mod-Space

## Managing Workspaces
* Switch to workspace n: Mod-n 
* Send current window to workspace n: Mod-Shift-n

## Managing workspace session
* Exit XMonad: Mod Shift-Q
* Reload new xmonad.hs configuration: Mod-q

## Configuration Management
* Recompile xmonad -- recompile
* Load new config file: Mod-q